<section class="page-hero">
  <div class="wrap">
    <p class="eyebrow">Grounded answers, a human behind them</p>
    <h1>Ask Lane</h1>
    <p class="lede lede--wide">Lane is Everlane&rsquo;s assistant. Ask a plain-English question about buying or selling in St.&nbsp;Petersburg &mdash; flood zones and insurance, a neighborhood, property taxes, where short-term rentals are actually allowed, or how the process really works &mdash; and get a grounded answer from Everlane&rsquo;s own sourced knowledge base, checked for accuracy and fair housing on every reply, with a real broker behind anything Lane can&rsquo;t answer.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" style="padding-top:10px">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="chat-panel">
      <div class="chat-panel__id">
        <span class="chat-panel__mark" aria-hidden="true">E</span>
        <span class="chat-panel__idtext">
          <span class="chat-panel__name">Lane</span>
          <span class="chat-panel__tag">Everlane&rsquo;s assistant &middot; a human behind them</span>
        </span>
        <span class="chat-panel__status">{% if askLive %}<span class="chat-panel__dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>Ready{% else %}Offline{% endif %}</span>
      </div>
      <div class="chat-body">
        {% if not askLive %}<p class="form-disabled-note" role="note">Preview &mdash; Lane is offline</p>{% endif %}

        {#- Chat surface. When askLive, /assets/ask.js wires the composer to the
            `ask` edge function; when not, the fieldset renders disabled (the honest
            coming-state) and no network path exists. COPY GUARD (kb-lint): never
            claim to search/access/be the MLS — kb/guardrails/mls-claims.yaml. -#}
        <div class="chat-log" role="log" aria-live="polite" aria-label="Conversation with Lane">
          <div class="chat-msg chat-msg--bot">
            <span class="chat-who">Lane</span>
            <div class="chat-bubble">Ask me about flood zones, a neighborhood, taxes, short-term-rental rules, or how buying and selling works in St.&nbsp;Pete. I answer only from what Everlane has published and sourced &mdash; and I&rsquo;ll hand you to Serge for anything I can&rsquo;t.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="chat-suggest" aria-label="Example questions">
          <span class="chat-suggest__label">Try</span>
          <button type="button" class="chip" data-q="What does flood zone AE mean for insurance?">Flood zone AE &amp; insurance</button>
          <button type="button" class="chip" data-q="Can I run an Airbnb in Gulfport?">Airbnb in Gulfport?</button>
          <button type="button" class="chip" data-q="How does the homestead exemption work?">Homestead exemption</button>
        </div>

        <form class="chat-form" novalidate>
          <fieldset{% if not askLive %} class="form-preview-disabled" disabled{% endif %}>
            <label for="ask-input" class="sr-only">Your question</label>
            <div class="chat-composer">
              <textarea id="ask-input" name="question" rows="1" placeholder="{% if askLive %}Ask a plain-English question…{% else %}Lane is offline in this preview.{% endif %}" maxlength="500"></textarea>
              <button type="submit" class="chat-send" data-submit>Ask</button>
            </div>
          </fieldset>
        </form>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="fine chat-fine">Lane runs under a hard spending cap with a privacy-safe query log &mdash; no names, emails, phone numbers, or addresses recorded, and no chat transcripts kept. <a href="/ai/">How this site runs &rarr;</a></p>
  </div>
  {% if askLive %}<script>window.__ASK_BASE__ = "{{ '/' | url }}";</script><script src="/assets/ask.js" defer></script>{% endif %}
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="wrap">
    {#- full-width stacked bands (operator 2026-07-10: not left/right) -#}
    <h2 style="font-size:1.3rem">What Lane can help with</h2>
    <ul style="margin:8px 0 26px;padding-left:20px;line-height:1.7">
      <li><strong>Flood zones &amp; insurance</strong> &mdash; what a zone means for a home, what changed after the 2024 storms, how coverage is priced.</li>
      <li><strong>Neighborhoods</strong> &mdash; the features, the flood story, and the housing stock of the areas we cover, chapter by chapter.</li>
      <li><strong>Property taxes</strong> &mdash; homestead, Save Our Homes, portability, and how the numbers actually work here.</li>
      <li><strong>Short-term rentals</strong> &mdash; where in Pinellas an Airbnb is actually permitted, municipality by municipality, with dates.</li>
      <li><strong>The process</strong> &mdash; buying steps and costs, and how a broker-prepared valuation differs from an instant online number.</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="stub-block">
      <strong>The honest posture</strong>
      <ul style="margin:8px 0 0;padding-left:20px;line-height:1.7">
        <li><strong>Grounded, not guessing.</strong> Lane draws on Everlane&rsquo;s published, sourced knowledge base &mdash; every fact dated &mdash; and is built to say &ldquo;I don&rsquo;t know&rdquo; and hand you to Serge rather than fill a gap.</li>
        <li><strong>It describes the place, never who &ldquo;belongs&rdquo; there.</strong> A fair-housing line Lane is built to and checked against &mdash; automatically, on every answer.</li>
        <li><strong>Not a listing search.</strong> For homes on the market it sends you to the <a href="/search/">search page</a>; live listing results arrive with the data feed. It never fabricates a listing.</li>
        <li><strong>Human-backed.</strong> It doesn&rsquo;t collect your details here and it never closes a deal &mdash; anything transactional goes to a free consult with the broker.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" style="padding-top:0">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="card">
      <p style="margin:0">Prefer a person right now? That&rsquo;s the right instinct for anything about your own move. <a href="/contact/">Book a free consult with Serge &rarr;</a> &middot; Or dig into the <a href="/guides/">buyer &amp; seller guides &rarr;</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
